# Google Drive (synced paths)

When organizing `~/Documents/Drive`, `~/Documents/School Drive`, or other synced Drive folders:

- **Light polish only** unless the user asks for detailed sorting (rename awkward folders, flatten accidental over-sorting, clearer names — not deep topic taxonomy).
- **Do not reorganize contents inside folders that are already curated**, including **`Noteful Backup`** (existing notebook/year layout stays).
- **Do not modify** folders whose names match **`Tran_Oliver_AY*`** (e.g. `Tran_Oliver_AY23-24`, `Tran_Oliver_AY24-25`, `Tran_Oliver_AY25-26`). Do not move files into or out of those folders unless the user explicitly asks.

Apply broader cleanup elsewhere only when the user requests Drive cleanup.
